criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Newly dignosised type 2 diabetes according to WHO criteria.glycated hemoglobin (HbA1c)
             was more than 10%;

          -  Seronegative for antibodies against insulin, islet cells and glutamic acid
             decarboxylase (GAD);

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Type 1 diabetes mellitus,presence of autoimmune diabetes indicated by antibodies to
             insulin, islet cells, and GAD；

          -  Gestational diabetes;

          -  patients with heart, liver, or renal function impairment;presence of severe infections
             or cerebrovascular disease;
